postcontent:
Hello everyone from ghost munitions I'd like to introduce our latest product to the ghost munitions line of brass and cleaning solutions. 

We are now manufacturing rotary tumblers for home reloaders and commercial companies alike. Here are the specs for our offerings 

We start out with an all steel frame welded together by hand right here in America. marathon county WI to be exact utilizing the best and as many made in America products as we can we assemble our tumblers in house. 

What about capacity? 

This is where YOU the customer has to do a little leg work.  We want to provide the most efficient tumblers we can not only with low energy motors and water sensible cleaning but we want to provide a product that fits you. Normally we use a tank constructed by hand from American made pvc. For our commercial guys these tanks are 8" in diameter and approximately 22" long giving you the flexibly to run 500 pcs of 9mm to 1500 cases of 5.56 brass. If you are just a hobbyist we also have you in mind we can customize a tank that best fits you for both production and space. These are not made in China machines that will break after a week and anyone that's used or seen a cement mixer for using stainless steel media knows they are loud and inefficient.  

We can make tanks from 6" x 10" to 8"x24" one thing to consider is weight. Utilizing about 4 gallons of water and approximately 30 pounds of pellet pins a full large tank can be as much at 80# not a problem for some but not everyone needs that kind of capacity. 

So what all do I get? 

Tumblers will ship fully assembled ready to use. All you'll need to do is fill your tank with brass and media a little dawn some lemi shine top it off with warm tap water and away you go. 

What about shipping? 

These bad boys are not light weighting in at approximately 75# or a hair over we would like to ship these as best we can for the most cost effective rates if you are located in Wi we would be more than happy to have you by the shop to pick yours up or we can deliver for fuel cost. Nationwide we will acquire a shipping quote before an order is finalized. 

How about price? 

Pricing is going to be $450 for our large tumbler and smaller tumblers will be slightly less. All tumblers are custom built by hand so no worries about "out of stock on that model but we have this one right here for a little more." That's not how we believe customers should be treated. 

If interested we would love to hear from you. 

We accept money orders, checks, PayPal and major credit cards processed via intuit go payments. 

Stand by for pictures coming soon 

Thanks and keep your head down. Ghost Munitions team

title: For Sale:  AR-15 (Matrix Aerospace/PSA/FN barrel) w/ red dot, Ergo grip, Blackhawk stock
postcontent:
Here's a good quality AR-15 that will serve you well. It's built on a Matrix Aerospace lower with a Palmetto State Armory upper and FN machine gun steel barrel (1:9 twist), a full auto BCG and a Blackhawk LPK, which includes an Ergo grip. This grip is much more comfortable than the standard grip and features a hollow interior for small parts/battery storage. I put a 2x red dot scope on the flat top rail. No rear iron sight. I've only run about 200 rounds through this before deciding my safe was too full.

This is not an entry-level AR -- Matrix Aerospace lowers are used in Ruger AR lines, and the Palmetto State Armory receivers get rave reviews for their quality. My other AR also has a PSA upper and has run 100%! The red dot is a "TAC Vector Condor." It's cheap -- very similar to the TruGlo 2x -- but it's worked well and held its zero just fine. I have it set up now for absolute co-witness, but if you want a riser, I have one I can part with for a little bit extra. This AR comes with 5 magazines -- two C-Product GI mags and three Magpul PMags (2 still in the package). 

ARs are cheap now, and this one is priced accordingly -- not as cheap as an Oracle or M&P Sport, but much less than an AR using these quality parts. I am not interested in trades. Thanks for looking.

Refuse to be a Victim Seminar

Saturday, April 12, 2014

Silver Dragon Martial Arts, 7881 SW Cirrus Dr Bldg 25D, Beaverton, OR 97008

Pre-Register Online: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/register.php?IDNum=36

Experts agree that the single most important step toward ensuring your personal safety is making the decision to refuse to be a victim. That means that you must have an overall personal safety strategy in place before you need it. Crime prevention information from this class can help you make yourself a less attractive target and keep you safe at home, work or in public settings. 

Improve your personal safety strategies with NRA's Refuse To Be A Victim® Program. 

In our four-hour class (a shorter overview class is also available) called Refuse To Be A Victim®, you can learn the personal safety tips and techniques you need to avoid dangerous situations and avoid becoming a victim. An overview of some of the material we cover is… Home Security
 Personal Security
 Automobile security
 Workplace Security
 Technological security 

The NRA's Refuse To Be A Victim program was developed by the women of the NRA in 1993 in response to women nationwide who requested crime prevention and personal safety information. This course was originally presented only to women by women who were NRA Certified Instructors. However, in 1997, the NRA Board of Directors elected to open this course to men as well, due to the program's relevance to all people. 

If you want to learn to be safe, but do not want to learn about guns, this course is for you. If you want to add safety information to your knowledge base to compliment your pistol safety, this class is also a benefit to you. We can also customize this class to fit audiences from young to old and varying abilities. 

More Information: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/schedule.php?IDNum=36

Ar500 is target material not to be used as body armor. This body armor with the 2 plates and the vest weighs a total of 12 pounds. title: For Sale:  SIG Sauer P226 (W. German) 9x19 mm + 3 Magazines
postcontent:
If you're looking for a full-size combat handgun for home, vehicle or the range, the SIG P226 is the one to own. This DA/SA P226 is made in "West Germany." It is marked SIGARMS INC. Tysons Corner, which dates it at 1985-1987. This vintage warhorse has always performed 100% and shoots great -- not one failure the entire time I've had it. Some SIG fans prefer the German-made guns because they're lighter, slimmer and have "better balance." I've owned both German and US-made and don't notice a difference when shooting, but it is true the German made slide is slimmer and lighter. 

I don't have the box (which for this model was a cardboard box), but I do have an original zipper-back 15 round magazine and two 18 round MecGar mags. Thanks for looking. Any shooter would be happy with this gun.
